---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — elect-rix.tech" description="AI-powered engineering by elect-rix. Full-stack builds, local LLM workflows, hands-on consulting.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">About</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">The builder behind the bots. What I do, how I work, and why local AI matters.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Who I Am</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          I'm elect-rix — a solo builder and AI engineer running a two-workstation development lab. I don't work at a big tech company. I don't have a team. What I have is two powerful machines, a stack of local AI models, and the obsessive drive to build things that work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">What I Do</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p><strong class="text-text">AI Integration —</strong> I wire large language models into real applications. Not demos — production systems that handle real workloads, maintain context, and deliver reliable results. Local models via Ollama, cloud APIs when needed, always with proper tooling and agent orchestration.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-text">Full-Stack Engineering —</strong> I build complete products from database to pixel. TypeScript, React, Astro, Node, Python — whatever fits the problem. I care about architecture, type safety, and performance.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-text">Cloud & DevOps —</strong> I deploy to AWS, Cloudflare, and self-hosted infrastructure. IaC, CI/CD, container orchestration, automated backups. If it breaks at 3am, it should fix itself.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-text">Consulting —</strong> I advise teams on AI strategy, architecture decisions, and hands-on implementation. I review code, design systems, and mentor engineers.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">How I Work</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p>I work from the Workstation Duo — two machines in my home lab. The primary workstation runs Pop!_OS with an RTX 5070 Ti for local LLM inference. The secondary handles distributed builds and GPU compute on Linux Mint. Everything is private by default. Your data never touches a third-party API unless you explicitly ask for it.</p>
          <p>I use AI as a collaborator, not a replacement. The models handle the boilerplate, the research, and the repetitive tasks. I handle the architecture, the edge cases, and the judgment calls. That's the only way to build systems that actually work.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Get in Touch</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">Interested in working together? Have a project that needs AI integration or full-stack engineering? Let's talk.</p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@elect-rix.tech" class="inline-flex items-center px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-accent text-white font-semibold hover:bg-accent-bright transition-colors">
          hello@elect-rix.tech
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
